<item>
            <title>[OAK-1968] Wrong time unit for async index lease time</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1968</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The JavaDoc for &lt;tt&gt;AsyncIndexUpdate.ASYNC_TIMEOUT&lt;/tt&gt; says the time unit for the timeout is minutes. Within the code the timeout value is rather interpreted as milliseconds, which looks wrong. E.g. the new lease value is calculated as &lt;tt&gt;lease = now + 2 * ASYNC_TIMEOUT&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
It is probably best to change the constant to reflect the timeout in milliseconds.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like this issue was introduced with changes for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1877&quot; title=&quot;Hourly async reindexing on an idle instance&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-1877&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-1877&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and affects the 1.0.1 and 1.0.2 releases.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
